<br>
But onto the thread - not every wizard 63+ is nuking for 2k+ on every nuke.<br>
<br>
The point is that a mage pet is now going to be even bigger for DPS.  Has anyone at SoE ever parsed an hours worth of time and seen Mage DPS (including their nukes and pet) and the wizards?  Did they take into effect the mages summoning ability and DS (which I think wizards should get better than that piece of crap 5pts DS) into any of these arguments?<br>
How about the tanking ability of a 4k+ pet?  The usualy argument back is wizards get root.<br>
<br>
We can go on and on.  My main argument is that I want to be seen as a DPS monster.  I want to push DPS to the point on wizards that everyone wants one in a group.  Not just burst - but something that we can sustain over a period of time.  Mages pets are a huge DOT.  So they can med during the DoT.  Don't give wizards that, give wizards better mana regen -even better when we are standing.  So that we can burst and sustain and maybe just put an end to the Mage vs. Wizard (or even the Druid vs. Wizard) discussions.<br>
<br>
Zigon<br>
<br>
ps. Milaru - don't forget - I will get you some candy. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=qaman>Qaman</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 3254<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/23/03 11:47 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:What about wizards?</span><hr size=1> &gt;The point is that a mage pet is now going to be even bigger for DPS. <br>
<br>
Actually, that isn't the point. They want the dps on the fire version of the mage pet brought into line with the other mage pets they already have. So that isn't adding anything. The main question is, how to bring that dps up without at the same time giving them new abilities that blur class lines even more and without overpowering the pet in some other way.<br>
<br>
&gt;Don't give wizards that, give wizards better mana regen<br>
<br>
You do realize that we already have pretty much the best stackable standing  mana regen available of any class in a lot of ways. More mana regen is always nice, but it doesn't address any of the things you are talking about.<br>
