Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=necridious>Necridious</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br>  Posts: 345<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/5/03 5:13 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:What about wizards?</span><hr size=1> Mage Fire pet is currently a joke.  They would have been better off if they had never made it a Wizard, and left it on the warrior template with a fire nuke that it was at &lt;=49.<br>
<br>
Though I agree it's crap they want to give a level 60 wizard pet Ice Comet... if anything, it's level 60 and should as a fire pet be casting Sunstrike, Pilliar of Fire, Tears of Ro, Draught of Fire, etc.  <br>
<br>
The main thing is that it be a Casting pet with a DPS around the same as the water pet, regardless of what it's casting so long as it's not crossing class too much--as giving mages the availability of large ice nukes does.  <br>
<br>
Water is melee dps, Fire is casting dps, Earth for damage absorbtion, Air for Damage mitigation--thus a pet for all occasions.  If the problem is that the pets in general are doing too much damage, that's a different discussion.  The mages current problem is that the Fire pet is a poorly designed Joke.<br>
<br>
And, like all DPS classes, Mages are not much more group friendly than Wizards.  Pets still give some people Heebie Jeebies, their summons are for the most part useless, so they contibute poorly to the group effort other than damaging a mob--just as we do.  You want better grouping options, tell Sony that's it's poor design to have the support classes have 200% more group utility while retaining 70+% of the dps. Or tell them that it's possible to code good Caster/Ranged attacker mob AI and that a mix of mob types would facilitate more strategys being used than the holy trinity where anything can be beat down given time.  Caster Mobs that activly kept their distance while raining down arrows/spells for mob type damage would indeed put the casters right back into the group.  <br>
<br>
Imagine the Horror of a holy trinity group trying to kill a wizard mob that BoF's a whole group, then proceeds to keep it's distance and even uses shadowstep when rooted, all the while raining down nukes or ae's on them, as opposed to idiot caster mobs that rain down random spells in no kind of tatical strategy.  Now imagine that same fight where the Wizard mob comes in, BoF's the group, and the DPS casters calmly start to cast their spells right back at the thing while the warrior attempts to keep as much aggro as possible using bows, knives and taunt.<br>
<br>
Personally, I'd laugh myself into a hemorrage watching a group of rogues and warriors get quadded by a wizard mob...if they were silly enough to keep trying to follow it. <p><br>
