<br>
I hate having the mob gate then summon a few people to it for private execution.  Or knowing it's just a matter of a few seconds and it will be back at full health for round 2, possibly with friends.  That's just Poor AI.<br>
<br>
If you were by yourself, and had to gate or abscond, would you immediatly run back to the same mob as soon as you hit half health?  Perhaps if you could get a few friends, but not by yourself and not right away, yet this is what the AI does.<br>
<br>
I have always felt that if the AI decides it's time to run or gate, then when it's out of range of the party, it's aggro list should be wiped and it should go home.<br>
<br>
Remember how stupid it was back when you were level 5, and you'd smack a spiderling which would instantly head for the hills.... till it got back to half health, then it would be back, and you'd smack it again, and it'd run agian, and again, and again... if the silly thing just lost aggro, it'd be alot better AI. <p><br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=448514">Antrygus Windrose </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=athousandyoung>AThousandYoung</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 5:11 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re:What about wizards?</span><hr size=1> LOL...I like the quadding mobs and Ranger mobs that bow kite players...<br>
<br>
That is one of the most glaring flaws of this game.  Decent mob AI needs to be implemented and the class mobs need to become fully class mobs and not tanks with spells or backstabs.<br>
<br>
Part of the problem here is that you cannot &quot;taunt&quot; players...a problem that Warriors have in PvP.  The game is designed in such a way that Jolt, Concussion, Taunt, Flame Lick, Disease Cloud, Evade, Feign Death etc are critical balancing factors which do not work when the mob (or player) is facing PCs.<br>
<br>
But if they tweaked it...imagine your group running into a Warrior mob with two Rogue mobs, a Cleric mob, an Enchanter mob and a Mage mob backing it...Warrior engages, keeps forcing it's target (whoever that is) to face and target it instead of chasing after the others (success based on mob taunt skill, target's Int/Wis, andmaybe  the amount of &quot;hate&quot; the PC has accumulated for different targets), Rogues keep moving behind the tank's target and vanishing from the target window when someone targets them, mage sends pet and nukes cautiously from a distance, Enchanter mezzes all but the tank's target, Cleric playing defensively and keeping the others alive...heh heh.  THAT would be a fun fight. <p>Caffron, Wizard of &lt;<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/bsanctuslumen" target="top">Sanctus Lumen</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->&gt;, the Good team PK guild.</p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showMessageRange?topicID=909.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showPrevMessage?topicID=909.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=909.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.emailToFriend?topicID=909.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm10.threadControl?topicID=909.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub140.ezboar